name: Vicki Li
title: pikachu
oneLiner: I'm not weird, I'm limited edition

entries.text: Nerf: New to the culture, not new to hunting people down in my fivefingers shoes. [You guys have no idea what you're getting into.]
Art: Sketching, Photoshopping, drawing on my arm... Worked on a visual novel with a friend at some point as well.
Dressing up, whether for fun or for show (cosplay included): Turns out make-up is like real-life Photoshop. Who knew?
Gaming (especially with other people): And easily 'rant-able' topic. Current favorites include League of Legends and..... yeah, League of Legends.
Coding under the influence [of caffeine and dubstep]: If my headphones are on and I'm unresponsive, it's because I challenge-accepted something.
Tutoring: Typically helping with math, essay-writing, or standardize tests (stop making faces, it's not that bad).
Talking a lot: Please tell me when to stop.
Obsession with languages/codes: Spent time memorizing braille, morse code, Elvish (Sindarin)... have since downgraded to animal noises/gibberish.
Being a rockstar: Was in a band with a few friends in high school, playing keyboard/keytar and also singing.
Martial arts: Spent some time in high school learning Aikido, which is self-defense. It's supposedly designed for short people...
Anime/Manga: Was interesting high school, but then it turns out it requires this thing called 'free time'.
Writing: Started with writing fanfiction with 3 other girls in middle school, ended up enjoying writing overall. (Not fanfiction anymore, though.)
